<h2>Assign Jenkins jobs to projects</h2>
Specify Jenkins jobs to a project by adding them seperated by a <i>;</i> (semicolon). Jenkins is a contineous integration sever, its jobs are build tasks within Jenkins.
It tests the assigned testcases, but it do not check the git version. Example for adding jobs: <i> job1;job2;job3 </i>
 <table style="min-width:100%">
  <tbody>
    
	
<% 
  projects = Project.all
  projects.each do |p|
  temp = p.identifier
 %> 
		<tr>
		<th style="min-width:15%">
			<%= temp%>
		</th>
		<td>
        <input type="text" id="settings_rjc_<%= temp%>" 
                           value="<%= settings["rjc_#{temp}"] %>" 
                           name="settings[rjc_<%= temp%>]" >
                           
		</td>
		</tr>
  <%end%>	
	
		
    
    
    
  </tbody>
</table>
